Attribute Name: TOTAL_CHECK

Related CTE(s):
BASE_SUM1, BASE_SUM2, base_sum_final

Source Fields Used:
Derived from aggregated application records using:
- QUOTE_STATUS_CODE
- AggregATOR_INDICATOR
- Decision / outcome fields (Accepted / Referred / Declined)
- Channel / On-us indicators

Technical Transformation Summary:
TOTAL_CHECK is calculated as a sum of multiple aggregated metrics representing different stages of the application journey, including API quotes, on-us eligibility checks, and quote-to-application transitions.

Business Logic:
Represents the total volume of eligibility checks and application-related records across the full customer acquisition journey. This includes initial aggregator quote checks, on-us eligibility checks, and records that progressed to applications.

Journey Stage:
Cross-journey metric covering:
- First Check (Aggregator / API)
- Second Eligibility Check (On-us)
- Final Application

Assumptions / Open Questions:
- It is unclear whether component metrics are mutually exclusive or overlapping.
- Confirm whether this metric is intended for reconciliation or reporting purposes.
- Validate alignment with the "Total Eligibility Checks" metric in the dashboard.